SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
a) Since \( f(x) \) is exponential, its formula will be \( f(x)=ab^x \).  Since \( f(0)= $a1 \) we know \( a = $a1 \) and thus \( f(x)=($a1)(b)^x \). $BR
Since \( f(1)= $f1_disp \ \), we have $BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ f(1) = ($a1) b^1 = $f1_math \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ $a1 b = $f1_math \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ b = $b1 \) $BR
So \( f(x)=$a1($b1)^x \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
b) We will find a formula for \( g(x) \) the same way.  Since \( g(0)= $a2 \) we know \( a = $a2 \) and thus \( g(x)=$a2(b)^x \). $BR
Since \( g(2)= $g1_disp \ \), we have $BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ g(2) = ($a2) b^2 = \frac{$a2}{$den2} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ b^2 = \frac{1}{$den2} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ b = \frac{1}{$g_bot} \) $BR
So \( g(x)=$a2 \left( \frac{1}{$g_bot} \right)^x \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
c) Since \( h(x) \) is linear, its formula will be \( h(x)=b+ mx \). We know that $BITALIC b $EITALIC is the $BITALIC y${EITALIC}-intercept, which is $a3, according to the graph.  Since the points (a,a+$a3) and (0,$a3) lie on the graph, we know that the slope, $BITALIC m${EITALIC}, is $BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \frac{(a+$a3)-$a3}{a-0} = \frac{a}{a} = 1 \), $BR
so the formula is \( h(x)= $a3+x \).
$BR $SPACE $BR 
d) We begin with $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ f(x) = g(x) \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ ($a1)($b1)^x = $a2 \left( \frac{1}{$g_bot} \right)^x \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \frac{$a1}{$a2} = \frac{(1/$g_bot)^x}{$b1^x} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \frac{$a1}{$a2} = \left( \frac{1}{$bot_sol} \right)^x \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \log{ \left( \frac{$a1}{$a2} \right) } = \log{ \bigg( \left( \frac{1}{$bot_sol} \right)^x \bigg) } \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \log{ \left( \frac{$a1}{$a2} \right) } = x \ \log{ \left( \frac{1}{$bot_sol} \right) } \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ x = \frac{ \log{ \left( \frac{$a1}{$a2} \right) }}{\log{ \left( \frac{1}{$bot_sol} \right) }} \) 
$BR
